    <h2 class="section-title">Complete Project Breakdown</h2>

    <div class="description-scroll">

      <h3>Project Overview</h3>
      <p>
        This is a real-time computer vision system built using YOLOv8 that captures live webcam input and performs object detection using deep neural networks.
      </p>

      <p>
        The system goes beyond simple detection. It records performance metrics, logs structured data, generates analytics, and produces AI-assisted reports that explain how the model behaves in real-world conditions.
      </p>

      <h3>System Architecture</h3>
      <p>
        Camera → Detection → Logging → Analytics → Visualization → AI Reporting
      </p>

      <h3>Execution Flow</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>System initializes YOLO model and logging pipeline</li>
        <li>Webcam captures frames in real time</li>
        <li>Each frame is processed through the detection engine</li>
        <li>Inference time is measured per frame</li>
        <li>Detection results are logged into structured CSV data</li>
        <li>Analytics module processes the dataset</li>
        <li>Charts and performance metrics are generated</li>
        <li>AI system analyzes results and produces a report</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Skill Set Demonstrated</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Computer Vision Engineering (YOLOv8)</li>
        <li>Deep Learning Inference (PyTorch)</li>
        <li>Performance Optimization & Benchmarking</li>
        <li>Data Logging & Analytics Pipelines</li>
        <li>Data Visualization (Matplotlib)</li>
        <li>AI API Integration</li>
        <li>Modular System Architecture</li>
        <li>End-to-End AI System Development</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Engineering Challenges Solved</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Maintaining real-time inference performance under continuous video input</li>
        <li>Reducing performance bottlenecks caused by logging and analytics</li>
        <li>Designing a system that collects data without impacting runtime speed</li>
        <li>Structuring modular components for scalability and testing</li>
        <li>Handling variability in detection outputs across different environments</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What I Bring to a Company</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ability to design scalable AI pipelines from scratch</li>
        <li>Strong understanding of performance monitoring and optimization</li>
        <li>Experience building full systems, not just isolated features</li>
        <li>Capability to transform raw data into meaningful insights</li>
        <li>End-to-end development from model execution to analytics and reporting</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Real-World Applications</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Security and surveillance systems</li>
        <li>Retail analytics and customer behavior tracking</li>
        <li>Autonomous vehicles and robotics</li>
        <li>Traffic monitoring and smart city infrastructure</li>
        <li>Industrial automation and defect detection</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Why This Matters</h3>
      <p>
        Companies don’t just need models — they need systems that are reliable, measurable, and scalable.
      </p>

      <p>
        This project shows the ability to build AI systems that can be deployed, monitored, and improved over time — exactly what production environments require.
      </p>

      <h3>Summary</h3>
      <p>
        This project transforms object detection into a full intelligent system capable of analyzing its own performance and generating insights.
      </p>

      <p>
        It demonstrates real-world AI engineering — not just running models, but building complete systems around them.
